text: Houghton County is a county in the Upper Peninsula in the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2020 census, the population was 37,361. The county seat and largest city is Houghton. Both the county and the city were named for Michigan State geologist and Detroit Mayor Douglass Houghton. ==References== Category:1840s establishments in Michigan Category:1846 establishments in the United States Category:Michigan counties
title: Houghton County, Michigan
